Operation O Kae Molao descended on Benoni on Thursday morning. eNCA's Nqobile Madlala joined the police and filed this report. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Almost 1,000 people, including 40 undocumented foreigners, have been arrested in Ekurhuleni. Operation O Kae Molao descended on Benoni on Thursday morning. The area is riddled with illegal mines. READ: EXCLUSIVE: Zama zama's violent world The police say abandoned mines in the area make it very attractive to Zama Zamas but they’re intent to keep an eye out for illegal activities. A similar operation on Wednesday night managed to net a suspect in the Rosettenville cash-in-transit incident. Police have also now revealed they disarmed an Operation Dudula member and while the firearm is licensed it will still have to go for ballistic tests.